
Use  “less” to open big files as it load page by page

Multiline comment in bash file   :  <<EOF  next-line script-here last-line EOF
   Multiline Comment with vim: :1,$ s/^/#/g ( substitute all lines start with # )
   Multiline comment using sed: sed -i.bkp ‘s/^/#/g’ myfile.sh ( .bkp is make the backup file )

Linux regular expression:
regex cheat sheet: https://remram44.github.io/regex-cheatsheet/regex.html
Test regex here: https://regexr.com/
use regex with : find, awk , sed, grep
use extended regular expression: grep -E
